Classes

CondenseQuestionChatEngine

CondenseQuestionChatEngine is used in conjunction with a Index (for example VectorStoreIndex). It does
two steps on taking a user's chat message: first, it condenses the chat message with the previous chat
history into a question with more context. Then, it queries the underlying Index using the new question
with context and returns the response. CondenseQuestionChatEngine performs well when the input is
primarily questions about the underlying data. It performs less well when the chat messages are not
questions about the data, or are very referential to previous context.

