Jina AI Reranker

The Jina AI Reranker is a postprocessor that uses the Jina AI Reranker API to rerank the results of a
search query.

<L=9T#2>Setup</L> <I=2>
Firstly, you will need to install the  llamaindex  package.

 

```typescript
pnpm install llamaindex
```

Now, you will need to sign up for an API key at Jina AI . Once you have your API key you can import the
necessary modules and create a new instance of the  JinaAIReranker  class.

 

```typescript
import {
  JinaAIReranker,
  Document,
  OpenAI,
  VectorStoreIndex,
  Settings,
} from "llamaindex";
```

<L=9T#3>Load and index documents</L> <I=3>
For this example, we will use a single document. In a real-world scenario, you would have multiple
documents to index.

 

```typescript
const document = new Document({ text: essay, id_: "essay" });
 
Settings.llm = new OpenAI({ model: "gpt-3.5-turbo", temperature: 0.1 });
 
const index = await VectorStoreIndex.fromDocuments([document]);
```

<L=9T#4>Increase similarity topK to retrieve more results</L> <I=4>
The default value for  similarityTopK  is 2. This means that only the most similar document will be
returned. To retrieve more results, you can increase the value of  similarityTopK  .

 

```typescript
const retriever = index.asRetriever({
  similarityTopK: 5,
});
```

<L=9T#5>Create a new instance of the JinaAIReranker class</L> <I=5>
Then you can create a new instance of the  JinaAIReranker  class and pass in the number of results you
want to return. The Jina AI Reranker API key is set in the  JINAAI_API_KEY  environment variable.

 

```typescript
export JINAAI_API_KEY=<YOUR API KEY>
```

 

```typescript
const nodePostprocessor = new JinaAIReranker({
  topN: 5,
});
```

<L=9T#6>Create a query engine with the retriever and node postprocessor</L> <I=6>
 

```typescript
const queryEngine = index.asQueryEngine({
  retriever,
  nodePostprocessors: [nodePostprocessor],
});
 
// log the response
const response = await queryEngine.query("Where did the author grown up?");
```

